      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "### Internal\n\n- Access Obsidian's bundled Moment.js through a `window.moment` wrapper (`src/core/moment.ts`) instead of `import { moment } from 'obsidian'`. This removes a spurious \"expression is not callable\" type error in editors/tooling that use `esModuleInterop: true`, and lets type-aware linting see the date code as fully typed rather than `any`. No user-facing behavior change.\n\n**Full changelog:** https://github.com/mattmcmanus/obsidian-moments/compare/0.5.1...0.5.2",
